together may thus be of help understanding how The Gourmand manages to come up with such a particular perspective.\r\n \r\nFood is the very source of inspiration both for Tweed and Lane, plus it has an invisible yet unbreakable, organic bond with all branches of art -and that’s exactly where The Gourmand takes off: Translating that bond to paper in all its visual presence. No need to say more; anybody who’s into innovative culinary culture should discover The Gourmand at once: A magazine that manages to stay away from cliches while exploring and celebrating food as an ultimate art form.','','','the-gourmand'),(36,36,'en','2013-10-30 22:06:59','2013-10-30 22:07:02','Odiseo','Odiseo is a publication for adult entertainment. It includes a selection of photographic stories with an erotic point of view, accompanied by cutting-edge ideas by contemporary thinkers. Volume 2 features Lina Schynius’ self portraits, Jo Schwab¡s “Habitual Grace”, and Amy Hood as seen by the lens of Jonathan Leder. It also includes a critical study on hipsterism today by Eugenia Lapteva, a long-distance call with Yuri Suzuki, and Timo Mashiyi-Veikkola’s view on collective identity in mass culture.','','','odiseo'),(37,37,'en','2013-10-30 22:06:59','2013-10-30 22:07:02','Bad Day','Bad Day Magazine brings together big hitters (this issue features Julie Doiron, Michael Snow and Ariel Pink; Jason Schwartzman is a big fan and past cover boy) with up-and-coming artists (such as previous LNB guest Tibi Tibi Neuspiel) from all cultural disciplines, both Canadian and international. \r\n\r\nEva Michon, Jackie Linton and Colin Bergh work together to produce and design this quarterly arts and culture publication that is distributed internationally and features beautiful photography and design as well as engaging interviews and articles. ','','','bad-day'),(38,38,'en','2013-10-30 22:06:59','2013-10-30 22:07:03','COPY OF Bad Day','Bad Day Magazine brings together big hitters (this issue features Julie Doiron,